            <!-- A New Perspective -->
            <section class="content-section">
                <h2 class="section-heading">A New Perspective on Cold Storage</h2>
                <p>
                    Dedicated hardware wallets serve a vital role, and <strong>SafeKeepVault</strong>
                    is designed to integrate seamlessly alongside them. However, for many users,
                    it&rsquo;s worth asking: is a $50&ndash;$250 specialized device the best use
                    of your money?
                </p>
                <p>
                    If you have a spare laptop on the shelf, or even the one you use daily, you already own what you need to safely store your Bitcoin. <strong>SafeKeepVault</strong> transforms that hardware
                    into a fully capable, air-gapped Bitcoin wallet for the cost of a thumb drive. By repurposing
                    the computer you&rsquo;ve already paid for, your money stays exactly where
                    it belongs&mdash;in Bitcoin.
                </p>
            </section>

            <!-- The OS is the problem -->
            <section class="content-section">
                <h2 class="section-heading">The OS is the Vulnerability, Not the Hardware</h2>
                <p>
                    Your laptop&rsquo;s hardware is a powerful tool; the true risk lies in the
                    software. Modern operating systems are
                    engineered for constant connectivity, telemetry, and background
                    processes&mdash;creating a broad attack surface for malware, keyloggers, and
                    remote exploits. This &ldquo;always-on&rdquo; architecture is the fundamental
                    opposite of what your private keys require.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <strong>SafeKeepVault</strong> solves this by swapping the software at the root.
                    By booting from an isolated USB drive, you bypass the insecure host OS
                    and its network vulnerabilities entirely. Your internal storage remains unmounted
                    and invisible, shielded from any potential compromise. When you are done, your computer returns to its original state with zero trace
                    of the vault&rsquo;s existence. 
                </p>
            </section>

            <!-- Principles -->
            <section class="content-section">
                <h2 class="section-heading">Our Core Principles</h2>
                <ul class="docs-list">
                    <li>
                        <strong>Sovereignty as a Standard &mdash;</strong>
                        Secure self-custody Bitcoin should not carry a high barrier to entry. The tools
                        required to protect your wealth should be free, open, and accessible to everyone.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Earned Trust, Not Assumed &mdash;</strong>
                        In a world of proprietary &ldquo;black box&rdquo; devices, transparency is
                        everything. Every line of our code is open-source, auditable, and verifiable.
                    </li>
            
                    <li>
                        <strong>Hardware Sustainability &mdash;</strong>
                        That &ldquo;old&rdquo; laptop is more than enough. We believe in maximizing
                        the utility of existing technology rather than creating more electronic waste.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>

